race.comment: Good race with loads of win chances. SCUSIES (9) made her debut in the rich Gold Rush at Bendigo and was only beaten three lengths. Given a good break and returns on the back of three hit-outs. Happy to give another go. GRINZINGER CHAMP (4) has fitness on her side and has given a sight at both runs, placing at each. Close to a maiden win and gets her chance. SEVEN OCEANS (10) ran well on debut before a spell, then was below that fresh when raced on speed but faded in slow going. Wide gate here but better than that and fitter again. Can improve sharply. GRANDSTRAZ (3) lines up for the first time since May 31. Started the last campaign in good style when in the placings over 1200m at Donald. Can make her presence felt. SKETCH (11) had two starts in NSW and resumes here for a new yard on the back of three hit-outs. This suits and can kick off with a big run.
